<item>
            <title>[LU-18461] Lustre join file re-implementation</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18461</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;So much workloads want to merge a several files in the one.  Long time ago - lustre had a &apos;JOIN file&apos; feature addressed it but it removed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once PFL exist it might be used to implement file join by adding components to a file with non-zero offset, but original PFL implementation has a bug/feature - which required start object from zero offset.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This prevents file join to use existing objects, and also caused troubles with large files on the ldiskfs backend.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s implement both features.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
